-- Latvian Budget Deficit Was 4% in 2011, Ministry Tells BNS
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-02-03T13:47:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/latvian-budget-deficit-was-4-in-2011-ministry-tells-bns.html
Latvia’s budget deficit was about 4
percent of economic output last year, according to preliminary
data, the  Baltic News Service  reported, citing Aleksis Jarockis,
a spokesman for the  Finance Ministry .  The figure is below the government’s target of 4.5 percent
of gross domestic product, BNS reported. Latvia will submit data
on the deficit to Eurostat on April 1, Jarockis said, according
to the Riga-based newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
